Mapping Portland’s Public Art

library(tidyverse)
library(leaflet)
public_art <- read.csv('public_art.csv')

topoData <- rgdal::readOGR(readLines("Neighborhood_Boundaries.geojson"), "OGRGeoJSON", verbose = FALSE)

pasteWord <- function(word, phr) {
  paste0('<strong>', word, ': ', '</strong>', phr)
}

popUpText <- function(data) { 
  paste0('<img src = ', data$image_url, ' style = "float:right;padding-left:5px">',
         paste(sep = '<br>',
               pasteWord('Title', data$title),
               pasteWord('Artist', data$artist),
               pasteWord('Year', data$date),
               pasteWord('Discipline', data$discipline),
               pasteWord('Medium', data$medium),
               pasteWord('Location', data$location))) 
  }

m <- leaflet(width = "100%", data = public_art, options = leafletOptions(minZoom = 11, maxZoom = 18)) %>% 
  setView(lng = -122.6541, lat = 45.5429, zoom = 11)

m %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addMarkers(data = public_art,
             ~lng, ~lat,
             popup = ~popUpText(public_art),
             popupOptions(maxWidth = 300),
             clusterOptions = markerClusterOptions(showCoverageOnHover = TRUE,
                                                   singleMarkerMode = TRUE)) %>%
  addPolygons(data = topoData,
              group = 'Neighborhood Boundaries',
              weight = 2,
              fill = TRUE,
              fillOpacity = 0.01,
              label = topoData$MAPLABEL,
              highlightOptions = highlightOptions(
                fillColor = "#03F",
                fillOpacity = 0.2,
                bringToFront = TRUE)) %>% 
   addLayersControl(overlayGroups = c("Neighborhood Boundaries"),
                    options = layersControlOptions(collapsed = FALSE)
  )
